---
description: Minimum accessibility checklist for UI changes
globs: **/*.{tsx,jsx}
alwaysApply: false
---

## A11y minimum (do every time)
- Every input has a **label** (visible or `sr-only`) and `id` wiring.
- Buttons/links have **clear text**; icon-only requires `aria-label`.
- Focus is visible (`focus-visible:*`), and keyboard navigation works.
- Use `aria-current`, `aria-selected`, `aria-expanded` where appropriate.
- Provide `alt` for meaningful images; `alt=""` for decorative.

## Forms
- Error message is connected via `aria-describedby`.
- Invalid state sets `aria-invalid="true"`.

## Tables/lists/menus
- Prefer native semantics first; only use ARIA roles when necessary.
